      "sc:citation": [
        "pubmed:40184383",
        {
          "@id": "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1012593"
        },
        "pmcid:PMC11970662"
      ],
      "sc:description": "TIPP3 is a metagenomic profiling method that solves the following problems:\n\nTaxonomic identification\nInput: A query read q\nOutput: The taxonomic lineage of q (if identified)\nAbundance profiling\nInput: A set Q of query reads\nOutput: An abundance profile estimated on Q\nTIPP3 continues the TIPP-family methods (prior methods: TIPP and TIPP2), which use a marker gene database to identify the taxonomic lineage of input reads (if the read comes from a marker gene). See the pipeline below for the TIPP3 workflow.\n\nAdditionally, TIPP-SD, as a subcommand, can perform detection at the species level.",
      "sc:name": "TIPP3",
      "sc:url": "https://github.com/c5shen/TIPP3"
    }
  ]
